ersive new introduction, a conversion of Hayek’s copious endnotes to footnotes, corrections to Hayek’s references and "ations, and the provision of translations to material that Hayek cited only in languages other than English—lends it new importance and accessibility. Rendered anew for the next generations of scholars, this revision of Hayek’s Law, Legislation, and Liberty is sure to become the standard.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aDemocracy. 0aEconomic policy. 0aLegislation. 0aLiberalism. 0aLiberty. 0aRule of law. 0aSocial justice. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aShearmur, Jeremy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226782003423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226782003/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles